            "<p><b>For numeric columns, you will see:</b></p>"
            "<ul>"
            "<li><b>Mean &amp; Median</b> -- Where is the 'centre' of the data? If mean ≠ median, "
            "the distribution is skewed.</li>"
            "<li><b>Std (Standard Deviation)</b> -- How spread out are the values? A std close to zero "
            "means values are tightly clustered around the mean.</li>"
            "<li><b>Min, Max, Range</b> -- The extremes of the data.</li>"
            "<li><b>Quartiles (Q1, Q3) &amp; IQR</b> -- The middle 50% of data. Critical for "
